\f2\b \cf4 Implementing Your Own CGI Script To Receive Crash Reports\
\pard\tx1160\li540\ql\qnatural

\b0\fs20 \cf0 \
If you wish to receive crash reports on your Web site, you can implement the custom Submit URL script that user's CrashReporter.app will contact directly. However, keep in mind that the following criteria should be met:\
\
	- Your web server script has to be in the same place over next several years, at the very least, to allow delivery of crash reports to you.\
	- You are responsible for adjusting the web script if the format CrashReporter.app sends crash reports in changes.\
	- Your web server should be accessible 24/7 and be on a reasonably fast connection to not delay user's submission process.\
\
For the above reasons, it is recommended to {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.unsanity.com/goto/email-ticket/"}}{\fldrslt obtain the email ticket}} from Unsanity and use the E-mail feature of Smart Crash Reports. Unsanity will make sure the server is accessible, knows how to parse all formats of submissions, and will safely redirect the crash reports to the email you provide.\
\
If your own Web script is still the way you want to go, here is the list of keys currently known to be passed to the script by the CrashReporter.app in a POST form data:\
\
	
\f3 \cf6 \CocoaLigature0 url_from
\f2 \cf0 \CocoaLigature1 : contains the subject of the crash report, usually "<Some Application> crash"\
	
\f3 \cf6 \CocoaLigature0 feedback_comments
\f2 \cf0 \CocoaLigature1 : user comments they entered in the additional info fields\
	
\f3 \cf6 \CocoaLigature0 bug_type
\f2 \cf0 \CocoaLigature1 : unknown constant, probably determines which POST elements are available; presently 9.\
	
\f3 \cf6 \CocoaLigature0 app_name
\f2 \cf0 \CocoaLigature1 : full crashed application name\
	
\f3 \cf6 \CocoaLigature0 app_version
\f2 \cf0 \CocoaLigature1 : version of the crashed application\
	
\f3 \cf6 \CocoaLigature0 os_version
\f2 \cf0 \CocoaLigature1 : Mac OS X version, in form 10.X.X:BUILD (for example, "10.4.2:8C46")\
	
\f3 \cf6 \CocoaLigature0 machine_config
\f2 \cf0 \CocoaLigature1 : Computer configuration string, for example, "PowerMac7,2 (2048 MB)"\
	
\f3 \cf6 \CocoaLigature0 page_source
\f2 \cf0 \CocoaLigature1 : Contains BASE64-encoded crash report\
	
\f3 \cf6 \CocoaLigature0 system_profile
\f2 \cf0 \CocoaLigature1 : Contains BASE64-encoded property list with a brief system profile of the user's system.\
\
Please note that these form keys are subject to change by Apple, so it is your responsibility to adjust the scripts on your Web servers if such thing happens. \
\
